Governor Samuel Ortom, on Wednesday, accepted the resignation of Rev. Emmanuel Aper as the Executive Secretary, Benue State Universal Basic Education, SUBEB. Emmanuel Aper had on Tuesday tendered his resignation letter to the State government. Reacting to the resignation, Ortom in a statement by the Secretary to the State Government, Professor Anthony Ijohor, SAN, appreciated the contributions Rev Aper made for the development of education in the state. The Governor wished him well in his future endeavours. Meanwhile, Aper has been directed to handover all government property in his custody to the Secretary to the State Government.